PRIOR ART NOTICE:

  This repository constitutes prior art in the following domains and
  applications as of the dates recorded in the git history (earliest
  commit: March 18, 2026):

  1. FORMAL VERIFICATION OF LEARNING THEORY
     Machine-checked proofs of the Fundamental Theorem of Statistical
     Learning (5-way equivalence), the Littlestone characterization of
     online learnability, Gold's theorem on identification in the limit,
     and all paradigm separation theorems with constructive witnesses.

  2. TYPE-THEORETIC STRUCTURE OF COMPUTATIONAL LEARNING
     Discovery and formal documentation of 3 irreducible type-theoretic
     fractures in learning theory (no common learner parent, no common
     data interface, five characterizations requiring five proof
     technologies) and 4 design tradeoffs.

  3. MEASURE-THEORETIC CORRECTIONS TO TEXTBOOK LEARNING THEORY
     Formal proofs that: (a) the No-Free-Lunch theorem is provably false
     for finite domains; (b) the standard branch-wise Littlestone tree
     definition admits a counterexample; (c) uniform convergence for
     uncountable concept classes requires NullMeasurableSet, not
     MeasurableSet; (d) quantifier ordering in uniform convergence is
     load-bearing for distribution-free guarantees.

  4. AI-ASSISTED FORMAL MATHEMATICS METHODOLOGY
     The methodology of type-architecture-first proof discovery using
     frontier language models (premise creation followed by supervised
     proof search within a pre-validated type structure), as documented
     in this repository and its companion repositories.

  5. FORMALIZATION TECHNIQUES FOR UNCOUNTABLE STRUCTURES
     The measurable inner event pattern, NullMeasurableSet integration
     lemmas, 7/12-fraction Chebyshev boosting, doubled-count arithmetic
     normalization, and three-step pullback chains for product-space
     measure transport, as implemented in this codebase.

  Any patent application, trade secret claim, or proprietary assertion
  covering techniques, results, or methods documented in this repository
  is subject to this prior art disclosure.

